# The conductor no longer auto-loads a committed .env. Its config — keys and
# storage — comes from the single local config at ~/.geostack/config, which you
# set through the app's Settings page (written 0600, never committed). A genuine
# shell env var still wins, for one-off dev overrides.
#
# Storage defaults to a local embedded file at ~/.geostack/geostack.db (zero
# config). To use Turso cloud instead, set these in Settings (or export them in
# your shell) — NOT in this file:
#
#   TURSO_DATABASE_URL   (turso db show <db> --url)
#   TURSO_AUTH_TOKEN     (turso db tokens create <db>)
#
# Optional dev overrides (export in your shell if needed):
#   PORT=8787
#   CORAL_SERVER_URL=http://localhost:5555
#   CORAL_TOKEN=local
#   GEOSTACK_READY_TIMEOUT_MS=90000
#   GEOSTACK_RESEARCH_TIMEOUT_MS=360000
#   GEOSTACK_SYNTHESIS_TIMEOUT_MS=900000
